\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 25. V. jordanii} Hanry,{\i  Prodr. Hist. Nat. Var} 169 (1853). Stems up to 40 cm, erect. Leaves cordate, dimorphic; the lower about as long as wide, the upper triangular-lanceolate, 2-3 times as long as wide. Stipules up to 4 cm, conspicuous, the lower dentate, the upper almost entire, equalling or exceeding petiole. Flowers c. 2·5 cm, pale blue or white; spur c. 5 mm, curved upwards. 2n = 40.{\i  Marshes and fens. S.E. & E.C. Europe; S.E. France.} Bu Ga Hu Ju Rm Rs (W, K).
