\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 26. V. uliginosa} Besser,{\i  Prim. Fl. Galic. }{\b 1}: 169 (1809). Rhizome slender; shoots short, erect, bearing rosettes of leaves. Leaves 4 × 2 cm, cordate, acute; petiole 2-10 cm. Stipules ovate-lanceolate, entire. Flowers 2-3 cm, arising from the base of the rosette, violet. Sepals 5-6 mm, ovate-lanceolate. Spur 3-4 mm, stout, violet. Fruiting peduncles up to 15 cm, erect. 2n = 20.{\i  Moorland and marshes. C. & W. parts of U.S.S.R. and S. & E. Fennoscandia, extending very locally westwards to E. Germany and N.W. Jugoslavia}. Da Fe Ge Ju Po ?Rm Rs (N, B, C, W) Su.
